<sn><md>### Automatic Favicon Detection

If you have a file named `favicon.ico` in the **root directory** of your website (e.g., `https://example.com/favicon.ico`),
most browsers will automatically detect and apply it even without a `<link>` tag.

**Example (automatic load):**

```
/favicon.ico
```

However, note that browsers can be **slow to update** cached favicons.
If you change the favicon, you might need to clear your browser cache or rename the file (e.g., `favicon-v2.ico`) to ensure the new icon appears.
